content.html:
I had to take today off work, because I ended up locking up my left shoulder and neck muscles so badly that I could not move without such terrible pain it put my to tears. I’ve had to end up taking some of my wife’s strong pain killers and muscle relaxants over the past couple of days.

Let this be a lesson to anyone working in this (IT) industry, it is highly important that you watch out for RST (repetitive strain injury) – And in my case (due to my vision impairment) it is important you avoid the use of laptops (of any kind) and stick to Desktops where you can sit more or less straight and not end up being lop-sided like I just did the past few weeks and caused my left shoulder to lock up quite badly 😢
